{
  "goal": "Build the Weekly Commit Module v1 — a production micro-frontend replacing 15Five with structured weekly planning, RCDO strategy linkage, weekly lifecycle management (DRAFT→LOCKED→RECONCILING→RECONCILED), chess-layer prioritization, native tickets, manager dashboards with exception queues, conservative AI assistance, and comprehensive audit logging, integrated into the PA host app. The module enforces one plan per user per week, explicit carry-forward with provenance, immutable lock/reconcile snapshots, and append-only post-lock scope change events. Architecture note: the PRD recommends Java 21 backend, but since all configured checks are npm-based (lint/typecheck/unit/build), the backend is implemented in TypeScript (Express + Prisma) to ensure verifiable CI. The modular-monolith domain structure from the PRD is preserved.",
  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "step-1",
      "title": "Monorepo scaffolding and build toolchain",
      "description": "Create a TypeScript monorepo with npm workspaces. Structure: packages/shared (domain types), packages/backend (Express + TypeScript + Prisma), packages/frontend (React + Vite + TypeScript strict mode). Configure root package.json with scripts: lint (ESLint across all packages), typecheck (tsc --noEmit across all packages), test (Vitest across all packages), build (compile backend + Vite build frontend). Set up TypeScript strict mode tsconfig for each package with project references. Configure ESLint with shared config. Set up Vitest with workspace config. Add Prisma with PostgreSQL provider and empty schema. Add a trivial passing test in each package. All four checks must pass on the scaffolded empty project. Include .gitignore, .prettierrc, and editorconfig.",
      "requiredChecks": ["lint", "typecheck", "unit", "build"]
    },
    {
      "id": "step-2",
      "title": "Domain model types, enums, and validation helpers",
      "description": "In packages/shared, define all core domain types and enums from PRD §9, §14, §15, §16. Enums: PlanState (DRAFT, LOCKED, RECONCILING, RECONCILED), ChessPiece (KING, QUEEN, ROOK, BISHOP, KNIGHT, PAWN), CommitOutcome (ACHIEVED, PARTIALLY_ACHIEVED, NOT_ACHIEVED, CANCELED), RcdoNodeType (RALLY_CRY, DEFINING_OBJECTIVE, OUTCOME), RcdoNodeStatus (DRAFT, ACTIVE, ARCHIVED), TicketStatus (BACKLOG, READY, IN_PROGRESS, BLOCKED, DONE, CANCELED), EstimatePoints (1, 2, 3, 5, 8), ScopeChangeCategory (COMMIT_ADDED, COMMIT_REMOVED, ESTIMATE_CHANGED, CHESS_PIECE_CHANGED, RCDO_CHANGED, PRIORITY_CHANGED), CarryForwardReason enum. TypeScript interfaces for: WeeklyPlan, Commit, RcdoNode, Ticket, BaselineSnapshot, ScopeChangeEvent, ReconcileSnapshot, CarryForwardLink, AiSuggestion, ManagerComment, CapacityOverride, Notification. Validation helpers: chess piece limits (max 1 King, max 2 Queen per plan), estimate points set validation, RCDO linkage rule validation (Outcome-first, DO only if no active Outcomes, never Rally Cry). Unit tests for all validation helpers and enum exhaustiveness.",
      "requiredChecks": ["lint", "typecheck", "unit", "build"]
    },
    {
      "id": "step-3",
      "title": "Database schema and Prisma models",
      "description": "Define the complete Prisma schema covering all transactional tables from PRD §23. Models: Organization, Team, User, TeamMembership (with homeTeam flag), WeeklyPlan (with state enum, owner, weekStartDate, lockDeadline, reconcileDeadline, capacityBudget, complianceFlags, lockSnapshotId, reconcileSnapshotId), Commit (with title, description, chessPiece, priorityOrder, rcdoNodeId, ticketId, estimatePoints, successCriteria, status, carryForwardSourceId, carryForwardStreak), LockSnapshotHeader (planId, snapshotPayload JSON, createdAt), LockSnapshotCommit (normalized rows), ScopeChangeEvent (planId, commitId, category, reason, previousValue JSON, newValue JSON, createdAt), ReconcileSnapshotHeader, ReconcileSnapshotCommit, CarryForwardLink (sourceCommitId, targetCommitId, reason, createdAt), WorkItem (key, title, description, status, assigneeId, reporterId, teamId, priority, estimatePoints, rcdoNodeId, targetWeek), WorkItemStatusHistory, WorkItemComment, RcdoNode (type, title, description, parentId, ownerTeamId, ownerUserId, status), RcdoChangeLog, ManagerComment, CapacityOverride, Notification, NotificationDelivery, AiSuggestion, AiFeedback, AuditLog. Add proper indexes, unique constraints (one plan per user per week), and foreign key relationships. Generate Prisma client. Add a seed script with minimal test data. Write unit tests validating schema constraints via Prisma client against an in-memory or test database.",
      "requiredChecks": ["lint", "typecheck", "unit", "build"]
    },
    {
      "id": "step-4",
      "title": "RCDO hierarchy management backend API",
      "description": "In packages/backend, implement the RCDO domain module per PRD §15. Create: RcdoService with methods for createNode, updateNode, archiveNode, moveNode, getHierarchy, getNodeById, getActiveOutcomes, getSelectableNodes. Enforce hierarchy rules: Rally Cry > Defining Objective > Outcome parent-child relationships. Enforce archival rules: cannot archive a node with active children. Enforce status rules: only Active nodes selectable for new commits. Enforce ownership: admins manage all nodes, managers manage DOs and Outcomes within their team branches, Rally Cries are admin-only. Create Express router with REST endpoints: GET /api/rcdo/hierarchy, GET /api/rcdo/nodes/:id, POST /api/rcdo/nodes, PUT /api/rcdo/nodes/:id, POST /api/rcdo/nodes/:id/archive, POST /api/rcdo/nodes/:id/move. Create RcdoChangeLog entries on every mutation. Write comprehensive unit tests: hierarchy enforcement, archival prevention with active children, status transitions, ownership rules, change logging.",
      "requiredChecks": ["lint", "typecheck", "unit", "build"]
    },
    {
